snippet: Mr. Bush is visiting Iowa this weekend for only the second time this year, and he has decided to skip the straw poll there in August.
abstract: Many veterans of presidential campaigns of the Bush family are worried that Jeb Bush and his team are planning to skip early and heavy campaigning in Iowa, state that was hallmark of both his father's and brother's campaigns; Bush is set to make only his second visit there in the year, and even some of his constituency and political establishment are worried about his prospects.
lead_paragraph: Mr. Bush is visiting Iowa this weekend for only the second time this year, and he has decided to skip the straw poll there in August.

headline.main: To Iowa G.O.P., Jeb Bush Appears to Be Ignoring the Family Playbook
headline.print_headline: To Iowa G.O.P., Jeb Bush Appears to Be Ignoring the Family Playbook
